{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> διατρίβω</b> [ρῑ], <br /> <i>perfect</i> <b>-τέτρῐφα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.57.3:\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist 2</i> διετρίβην [ῐ] (see. below):—<b>rub hard,</b> χερσὶ διατρίψας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.847 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: more frequently, <b>wear away, consume,</b> πάντα διατρίβουσιν Ἁχαιοί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.265; χρήματα 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 921; τὰ τῶν Πελοποννησίων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.87 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς αἰτίας ἀλόγους δ. τὸ θεῖον <b>to fritter away</b> Providence into unreasoning causes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Nicias” 23:\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] — <i>passive</i>, κάκιστα διατριβῆναι <b>perish</b> utterly, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.120 (variant{ἐκ-}),compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.78. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>spend,</b> of Time, θερείην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.189; frequently χρόνον δ. 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 3.11; παρά τινι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.24, etc.; δ. τινὰς ἡμέρας 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.5.49; ἓξ ἔτη 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.141 (later with _genitive_, ἐτῶν οὐκ ὀλίγων ἐν Ῥώμῃ δ. 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 3.10.2)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, ἐνιαυτὸς διετρίβη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.125. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i> (without χρόνον), <b>waste time,</b> οὐ μὴ διατρίψεις..; <b>make</b> no more <b>delay,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 462 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ἐν γυμνασίοις <b>pass all one's time</b> there, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Nu.” 1002; ἐν ἄστει 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.14; ἐν ἀγρῷ 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 71.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐτοῦ, ἔνδον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 311a; δ. μετ᾽ ἀλλήλων \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>go on talking,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phd.” 59d, etc.\">Refs</a>]: hence, <b>busy, employ oneself,</b> ἐν ζητήσει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ap.” 29c; ἐν φιλοσοφίᾳ [prev. author] “Tht.” 173c; ἐπί τινι [prev. author] “Euthd.” 305a, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.19, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.16; ἀμφί τι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 2.1; περί τι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 90c, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.4; πρὸς ἱππικῇ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 126c; πρὸς τοῖς ἔργοις 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1309a8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρὸς φιλοσοφίᾳ (probable reading for -ίαν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 540b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, δ. μελετῶσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.12. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>lose time, delay,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.150, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τῶν ἐν κεφαλη—ͅ τρωμάτων” 19, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 515, etc.; λέγε καὶ μὴ διάτριβε 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 472b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; διατέτρῐφα I <b>have let the time slip by..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tht.” 143a: with \">Refs</a>]<i>participle</i>, καθ᾽ ἕκαστα λέγων δ. <b>to waste time</b> in speaking, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.35, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 1.9. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>reside,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PHal. 1.182 (3rd c.BC), “PStrassb.” 22.6 (2nd c.AD), etc. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>put off by delay, thwart, hinder,</b> μή τι διατρίβειν ἐμὸν χόλον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.42; οὔ τι διατρίβω μητρὸς γάμον 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.341; τἄριστον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 503:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] with <i>double</i> <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i> et _of things_, ὄφρα κεν ἥ γε διατρίβῃσιν Ἀχαιοὺς ὃν γάμον <b>put</b> them <b>off</b> in the matter of her wedding, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.204:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] with <i>genitive</i> _of things_, μὴ δηθὰ διατρίβωμεν ὁδοῖο <b>let us</b> not <b>lose time</b> on the way, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 404 \">Refs</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, μή τι διατριβώμεθα πείρης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 2.883. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1304","accentedUnicode":"διατρίβω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1223","matchingForm":"διά","stepTransliteration":"dia","gloss":"through/because of","_zh_tw_Gloss":"藉著, 因, 為 …","_es_Gloss":"a través/por ","_zh_Gloss":"借着, 因, 为 …"},{"strongNumber":"G5147","matchingForm":"τρίβος","stepTransliteration":"tribos","gloss":"path","_zh_tw_Gloss":"路","_es_Gloss":"camino","_zh_Gloss":"路"}],"shortDef":"to stay, remain, spend some time","mediumDef":"to stay, remain, spend some time <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>to rub, wear away by friction;</b> <i>metaphorically</i> <b>to pass</b> or <b>spend</b> time, <b>to remain, stay, tarry, continue,</b> <ref='Jhn.3.22; 11:54'>Jn. 3:22; 11:54</ref>; <ref='Act.12.19'>Acts 12: